724477f-a.title: Manhattan: West End Avenue - 100th Street (West)
724477f-a.text:
P30, 832, and 834-6 West End Avenue, east side, between 100th and
101st Streets.
P34-6, together with 838, the corner house at 101st Street, are
shortly to be replaced by The Dallieu, a 12-story apartment build-
ing, and 832, the narrow house, will simultaneously be demolished.
830 West End Avenue, together with the other three buildings in the
southern half of the block, not shown here, will stand until
replaced by the synagoguo Temple Ansche Chesed (3pened May, 1928).
About 1911.
MAY BE REPPODUCED.
